      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "Offering a museum-grade 1997 Acura Integra Type R in iconic Championship White. This example features the hand-built B18C5 engine, boasting factory-polished intake ports and high-compression pistons that deliver a linear power band up to its 8,400 RPM redline. The close-ratio five-speed manual gearbox operates with mechanical perfection, coupled with the original helical limited-slip differential for neutral handling characteristics. The chassis retains its structural integrity with all factory-specific spot welds intact and zero evidence of torsional fatigue. The suspension utilizes original geometry with pristine bushings and the signature rear subframe reinforcement. This is a concourse-level specimen with a completely dry undercarriage and an unmolested engine bay, representing the zenith of naturally aspirated VTEC performance.",
